original: Johannesson, Josef Ragnar, tandläkare, Kalmar, f. 3/12/07 i Oskarshamn av virkeshandl. Adolf J. o. Fredrika Lindström. G. 38 m. Wasti Herne. Barn: Håkan f. 39, Bengt 42, Per 45. — Stud:ex. i Kalmar 26, med. kand. i Upps. 31, tandl. 33. Prakt, i Kalmar sed. 34. Sekr. i Kalmar 1. tandl :sälls’k. 36-37. Hobbies: jakt o. fiske.
translated: Johannesson, Josef Ragnar, dentist, Kalmar, born on December 3, 1907 in Oskarshamn to timber merchant Adolf J. and Fredrika Lindström. Married in 1938 to Wasti Herne. Children: Håkan born in 1939, Bengt in 1942, Per in 1945. Completed secondary school in Kalmar in 1926, obtained a bachelor's in medicine in Uppsala in 1931, and graduated as a dentist in 1933. Started practicing in Kalmar in 1934. Secretary of the Kalmar Dental Association from 1936-1937. Hobbies: hunting and fishing.
